A juvenile Large Brown Spitting Cobra (Naja ashei), photographed at the Bio-Ken Snake Farm in Watamu, Kenya. These snakes look like a Black-Necked Spitting Cobra as juveniles and transition to a brown color as they grow. World's largest species of spitting cobra!

Large Brown Spitting Cobra (Naja ashei), Adult, being moved back to it's cage after cleaning. This snake was collected in Watamu and kept at the Bio-Ken Snake Farm and snake venom research facility in Watamu, Kenya. This species is the world's largest spitting cobra, and was officially recognized as a new species distinct from the Black-Necked Spitting Cobra (Naja nigricollis) in 2007. Bio-Ken described and discovered the species and it is named after Bio-Ken founder and legendary snakeman James Ashe.
